				<div class=3D"elementor-widget-container">
									<p><!-- /wp:post-content --><!-- wp:paragraph --></p>
<p>Cross correlation mathematically measures the similarity of signals. Con=
sider an example where you have a set of data samples represented by x[n] a=
nd y[n]. Cross correlation is used to measure on a sample by sample basis h=
ow similar x[n] is to y[n]. Simple examples with plots will demonstrate dif=
ferent combinations of positive, negative, strong and weak correlations.</p=
>
