				<div class=3D"elementor-widget-container">
									<p>Correlation is a way to mathematically measure similarity of tw=
o sequences. A large positive correlation means the two sequences are simil=
ar whereas a large negative correlation means the two sequences are similar=
 but have opposite polarity. A small correlation value, positive or negativ=
e, means the two sequences share few similarities. A correlation value of z=
ero means the two sequences do not share any similarities.</p>
